%pyspark
from pyspark.sql.types import *

class CTDLoader(object):
    def __init__(self, path, table, sample_size=1.0):
        self.path = path
        self.rdd = self.load (sample_size=sample_size)
        self.rdd.toDF().registerTempTable (table)
    def load (self, sample_size=1.0):
        return sqlContext.read.                                     \
            format('com.databricks.spark.csv').                     \
            options(comment='#').                                   \
            options(delimiter=",").                                 \
            options(header='true').                                 \
            load(self.path).rdd.                                   \
            sample (False, sample_size, 1234)
class CTDExposureEvents(CTDLoader):
    def __init__(self, path, table):
        CTDLoader.__init__(self, path, table)
class CTDGenesPathways(CTDLoader):
    def __init__(self, path, table):
        CTDLoader.__init__(self, path, table)
    
ctd_expo_data = '/projects/stars/translator/var/ctd/CTD_exposure_events.csv'
ctd_exposure_events = CTDExposureEvents (ctd_expo_data, 'ctd_exposure_events')

ctd_genes_pathways_data = '/projects/stars/translator/var/ctd/CTD_genes_pathways.csv'
ctd_gene_pathway = CTDGenesPathways (ctd_genes_pathways_data, 'ctd_genes_pathways')

prefix = { 
    'kegg' : 'http://www.genome.jp/kegg-bin/show_pathway?hsa',
    'ncbi' : 'https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/gene/'
}

pm25_agent_id = 'D052638'
asthma_mesh_id = 'D001249'

%sql 
select stressoragentid,receptordescription,phenotypeid 
from ctd_exposure_events 
where stressoragentid='D052638' and receptordescription like '%[D001249]%' order by phenotypeid
